      contentEn: `<p>I'm sure you've all seen it at least once... the white cat with one paw raised. The Maneki Neko (Beckoning Cat) is a ubiquitous symbol of luck in Japan.</p><p>But did you know the paw matters? Left paw invites customers, right paw invites money. At Artbar, we love painting these lucky charms in our own unique styles, sometimes adding sunglasses or vivid colors to modernize the tradition.</p>`,
